                <div class="faq-q">What are ETF fund flows?</div>
                <div class="faq-a">ETF fund flows refer to the net amount of money moving into or out of an Exchange Traded Fund over a specific period. Positive flows (inflows) indicate investors are buying and creating new shares, while negative flows (outflows) indicate selling and redemption of shares.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
